      <div class="details hidden">
          <div class="de1">
            <h2>System Requirements</h2>
            <p> 
              <ol>
                <li>A modern web browser (Google Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge).</li>
                <li>Internet connection.</li>
                <li>Python 3.x installed on your machine</li>
                <li>Required Python libraries: Flask, translate, gtts, SpeechRecognition, pyaudio</li>
                
              </ol>
              
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="de2">
            <h2>Local Machine</h2>
            <p>
              Open your web browser.<br>
              Navigate to http://127.0.0.1:5000/ to access the application.<br>
              Click the Speak button.<br>
Allow the browser to use your microphone if prompted.<br>
Speak clearly in Tamil.<br>
The spoken text will appear in the first textbox.<br>
Click the Hear Text button.<br>
Click the Translate to English button.<br>
The Tamil text in the first textbox will be translated to English and displayed in the second textbox. <br>
The translated text will be read aloud automatically. <br>
            </p>
          </div>
        
      </div>
